A:/> C:
C:/> # Create test files for multifile tests
C:/> 
C:/> # 4 files of 512 bytes each (1 block) with different seeds
C:/> 
C:/> RANDDATA FILE1.TMP 512 1
64291 1
C:/> 
C:/> RANDDATA FILE2.TMP 512 2
64064 1
C:/> 
C:/> RANDDATA FILE3.TMP 512 3
64985 1
C:/> 
C:/> RANDDATA FILE4.TMP 512 4
63865 1
C:/> 
C:/> # 2 files of 1024 bytes each (2 blocks) for interleaved test
C:/> 
C:/> RANDDATA FILEA.TMP 1024 100
59809 2
C:/> 
C:/> RANDDATA FILEB.TMP 1024 200
59690 2
C:/> 
C:/> #
C:/> 
C:/> # Test 1: Open 4 files simultaneously, read each, print checksums
C:/> 
C:/> multifile.app 1
Test 1: Multi-open read
64291
64064
64985
63865
OK
C:/> 
C:/> #
C:/> 
C:/> # Test 2: Interleaved reads vs sequential reads
C:/> 
C:/> multifile.app 2
Test 2: Interleaved I/O
Interleaved sum A: 59808
Interleaved sum B: 59689
Sequential  sum A: 59808
Sequential  sum B: 59689
OK
C:/> 
C:/> #
C:/> 
C:/> # Test 3: Handle exhaustion and recovery
C:/> 
C:/> multifile.app 3
Test 3: Handle exhaustion
Handles opened: 7
Exhaustion error: 6
Recovery: open after close succeeded
OK
C:/> 
C:/> #
C:/> 
C:/> # Cleanup
C:/> 
C:/> RF FILE1.TMP
C:/> 
C:/> RF FILE2.TMP
C:/> 
C:/> RF FILE3.TMP
C:/> 
C:/> RF FILE4.TMP
C:/> 
C:/> RF FILEA.TMP
C:/> 
C:/> RF FILEB.TMP
C:/> 
C:/> HALT
CPU halted
